BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Sex and Dissent: Stories of Feminist Resistance in Argentina\, Ch
 ile\, Mexico\, and Spain" by Meaghan Beatley
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260311T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260311T200000
DTSTAMP:20260309T062309Z
UID:b285ae9d6ae674af@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Part of the Feminism in Theory and Practice Series.\n\nSex and
  Dissent: Stories of Feminist Resistance in Argentina\, Chile\, Mexico\, a
 nd Spain offers four electrifying and hopeful accounts of feminist uprisin
 g that have swept through Latin America and Spain in the wake of #MeToo—
 and what we can learn from these protest cultures in a fraught moment for 
 democracy in the U.S.\n\nAs women’s rights have faced alarming rollbacks
  in the United States over the past decade\, mass feminist movements beyon
 d our borders have achieved historic victories. Award-winning journalist M
 eaghan Beatley takes us to the frontlines to tell inspiring stories of res
 istance and political imagination that will be a vital roadmap in the year
 s to come. A national reckoning over abortion in Argentina\; a constitutio
 nal rewrite confronting structural inequality in Chile\; a high-profile se
 xual assault case in Spain that sparked wide debate about consent\; and in
  Mexico\, student protesters forcing a national spotlight on the epidemic 
 of femicide. \n\nThe product of a decade of immersive reporting\, Beatley 
 captures the urgency and creativity of these movements and the women who l
 ed a motley crew of former guerrilla fighters\, student occupiers\, and mo
 thers standing down narco violence. \n\nOrganized by Writer in Residence M
 oira Donegan\, the Feminism in Theory and Practice series welcomes contemp
 orary creators\, writers\, scholars\, and activists whose work challenges 
 gender inequality in urgent and innovative ways.\n\nRSVP for this online e
 vent\n\nAuthor Bio:\n\nMeaghan Beatley is a French and U.S. journalist cov
 ering feminist movements across Latin America and Spain. Her reporting has
  appeared in Time\, The Guardian\, The Atlantic\, The Nation\, and Foreign
  Policy. Formerly an editor in Chile and Argentina\, she has reported from
  seven countries and won the One World Media Award for Best Feature. She i
 s fluent in French\, English\, and Spanish\, and her work bridges language
 s\, cultures\, and continents.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.stanford.edu/e
 vent/feminism-in-theory-and-practice-featuring-meaghan-beatley-author-sex-
 and-dissent\n\nSource: stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/feminism-in-theory-and-practice-feat
 uring-meaghan-beatley-author-sex-and-dissent
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: "Sex and Dissent: Stories of Feminist Resistance in 
 Argentina\, Chile\, Mexico\, and Spain" by Meaghan Beatley
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
